https://rogerwelin.github.io/rpm/rpmbuild/2015/04/04/rpmbuild-tutorial-part-1.html

- to determine what system variable for rpm are:
    rpm --eval %{_bindir}


create a directory with your source 
   packer-1.6.5/packer
   tar cvfz packer-1.6.5-0.tar.gz



rpmbuild -bb rpmbuild/SPECS/packer.spec

gpg --list-keys

in ~/.rpmmacros
%_gpg_name Jeanne Greulich SIMP RPM Signing key (Key used to signed packages for install on systems) <jeanne.greulich@onyxpoint.com>

rpm --addsign <packagename>
